5
00:01:28,260 --> 00:01:29,890
我向你们发誓
I swear to you,

6
00:01:29,930 --> 00:01:33,160
每一个被瘟疫带走的母亲和女儿
every single mother and daughter,

7
00:01:34,230 --> 00:01:37,830
父亲和儿子
father and son taken from us

8
00:01:37,870 --> 00:01:40,670
我都将替他们一一报仇
by the Black Plague will be avenged.

9
00:01:43,810 --> 00:01:46,040
是黑巫后
It is their Witch Queen

10
00:01:46,070 --> 00:01:49,080
将诅咒降临在我们的大陆
who brought this curse upon our lands.

11
00:01:50,380 --> 00:01:53,350
只有她的死亡才能换来我们的救赎
And in her death lies our salvation.

12
00:01:58,050 --> 00:02:00,320
要注意 兄弟们
Be warned, brothers.

13
00:02:00,360 --> 00:02:02,720
在心脏停止跳动前
She will never truly perish

14
00:02:02,760 --> 00:02:06,360
她永远不会真正死亡
until her heart beats its last.

15
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:08,730
我们要无所畏惧
Let fear be dead to us.

16
00:02:08,760 --> 00:02:11,230
绝不能后退
There is no going back,

17
00:02:11,270 --> 00:02:14,140
因为我们已经无路可退
for there is nothing to go back to.

18
00:02:26,980 --> 00:02:29,450
那是什么 多兰?
What is it, Dolan?

19
00:02:35,860 --> 00:02:38,230
毁灭巫师就在我们身边
The Hexen are amongst us.

20
00:02:41,800 --> 00:02:44,070
这地方到处都是死亡的气息
This place reeks of death.

21
00:02:44,100 --> 00:02:45,470
时刻保持头脑冷静
Keep your wits about you.

22
00:02:45,500 --> 00:02:47,440
跟紧一点
Stay close.

23
00:02:51,970 --> 00:02:53,210
是她!
It's her!

24
00:02:53,240 --> 00:02:55,210
是黑巫后!
It's the Queen!

25
00:03:05,020 --> 00:03:06,990
是魔法
The magic.

26
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:15,430
后退!
Stay back!

27
00:03:36,990 --> 00:03:39,920
以钢铁和火焰之名!
By iron and fire!

28
00:03:42,090 --> 00:03:44,030
救救我们!
Help us!

29
00:03:49,230 --> 00:03:51,170
- 多兰! - 黑女巫!
- Dolan! - The Queen!

30
00:04:07,250 --> 00:04:08,980
天父啊
Heavenly Father,

31
00:04:09,020 --> 00:04:10,550
保佑我们远离这些魔鬼
protect us from these demons.

32
00:04:15,020 --> 00:04:17,460
啊!
Ah!

33
00:04:22,230 --> 00:04:24,500
保持阵型 兄弟们!
Stay in formation, men!

34
00:04:44,190 --> 00:04:45,990
父亲!
Father!

35
00:04:46,020 --> 00:04:47,960
父亲!
Father!

36
00:04:49,490 --> 00:04:53,600
父亲 我好想你
Father, I missed you.

37
00:04:53,630 --> 00:04:55,230
你不是真的
You're not real.

38
00:04:55,260 --> 00:04:57,570
不可能是真的
You can't be.

39
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:34,000
你们像老鼠一样繁衍
You breed like rats.

40
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:35,500
你们住在用岩石堆垒
You put stone on top of stone

41
00:05:35,540 --> 00:05:38,040
建成的肮脏巢穴里
and then live in your own filth.

42
00:05:38,070 --> 00:05:42,080
你们是我们世界的入侵者
You are trespassers on our world.

43
00:05:42,110 --> 00:05:45,980
因此我创造了瘟疫
This is why I created the Plague.

44
00:05:46,010 --> 00:05:50,320
你们每个人都必将毁灭
It's why every one of you must perish.

45
00:06:24,020 --> 00:06:26,720
啊!
Ah!

46
00:06:38,100 --> 00:06:40,030
以钢铁
By iron

47
00:06:43,610 --> 00:06:45,410
和火焰之名
and fire.

48
00:06:45,440 --> 00:06:48,040
你爱的每个人都离你而去
Everyone you love is gone.

49
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:50,550
我从你眼中就能看出来
I've seen it in your eyes.

50
00:06:50,580 --> 00:06:53,380
你渴望死亡
You wish for death.

51
00:06:53,420 --> 00:06:55,550
今天我们将同归于尽
Today we both die.

52
00:07:11,270 --> 00:07:13,800
我用我的生命诅咒你
I curse you with life.

53
00:07:15,140 --> 00:07:18,310
你将永世不得安宁
To never know peace.

54
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:23,780
你将孤独地走向世界的尽头
To walk the Earth alone for eternity.

55
00:07:27,420 --> 00:07:32,290
你将永远无法死亡
You will never die.

56
00:08:04,290 --> 00:08:06,320
谢谢
Thank you.

57
00:08:09,760 --> 00:08:11,830
打扰了 小姐?
Excuse me, miss?

58
00:08:11,860 --> 00:08:14,200
先生 有什么事吗?
Sir, how can I help you?

59
00:08:42,190 --> 00:08:44,130
魔法
Magic.

60
00:09:23,770 --> 00:09:25,700
嘿...
Hey...

61
00:09:26,770 --> 00:09:27,940
小心点!
Watch it!

62
00:09:27,970 --> 00:09:30,570
抱歉 都是我的错
Sorry. Totally my fault.

63
00:09:32,610 --> 00:09:34,780
不好意思
Excuse me.

64
00:09:39,820 --> 00:09:40,780
你是巫师猎人
You're the witch hunter.

65
00:09:40,820 --> 00:09:42,680
是的
Yeah.

66
00:09:42,720 --> 00:09:43,950
我什么都没做
I didn't do anything.

67
00:09:43,990 --> 00:09:45,450
给我看看
Let's see it.

68
00:09:45,490 --> 00:09:47,560
看什么?
See what?

69
00:09:47,590 --> 00:09:48,760
快点
Come on.

70
00:09:52,730 --> 00:09:53,760
女士们先生们
Ladies and gentlemen,

71
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:55,300
机长已经开启...
the Captain has turned on...

72
00:09:55,330 --> 00:09:57,770
幸亏你没把它们弄湿
Be glad you didn't get them wet.

73
00:10:00,370 --> 00:10:02,700
我找这东西有一阵子了
I've been looking for these for a while.

74
00:10:02,740 --> 00:10:04,910
这些都是古代符文
These are ancient runes.

75
00:10:04,940 --> 00:10:06,610
可以操纵天气
They can manipulate weather.

76
00:10:06,640 --> 00:10:09,480
雨 风 寒 炎...
Rain, wind, cold, heat...

77
00:10:09,510 --> 00:10:12,580
而你就这么把它们一起塞在包里?
And you just jammed them together in your bag?

78
00:10:12,610 --> 00:10:14,220
你知道当你把暴风雨符文和湿气符文
You know what you get when you mix a thunderstorm

79
00:10:14,250 --> 00:10:16,350
在40000英尺的高空混合起来后会得到什么吗?
with cool, moist air at 40,000 feet?

80
00:10:18,820 --> 00:10:20,560
这是很简单的科学道理
It's simple science.

81
00:10:27,400 --> 00:10:29,460
简直难以置信
Unbelievable.

82
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:33,200
你们这些巫师都不知道自己有着怎样的力量
You witches have no idea the power you've got.

83
00:11:21,650 --> 00:11:23,650
哦 天啊
Oh, my God.

84
00:11:25,990 --> 00:11:27,690
你要把我送到巫师委员会去吗?
Are you gonna turn me over to the Witch Council?

85
00:11:27,720 --> 00:11:29,360
不
No.

86
00:11:29,390 --> 00:11:30,990
那你会杀了我吗?
You're gonna kill me?

87
00:11:31,030 --> 00:11:33,660
杀你?
Kill you?

88
00:11:33,700 --> 00:11:36,530
我是在阻止你杀了你自己
I'm tryin' to stop you from killing yourself.

89
00:11:38,630 --> 00:11:40,700
祝你在纽约玩儿得开心
Enjoy New York.

90
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:45,310
先生 "请系好安全带"的标志亮了
Sir, "Fasten seatbelts" signs are on.

91
00:11:45,340 --> 00:11:46,310
你得回到座位上去
I need you to take a seat.

92
00:11:46,340 --> 00:11:48,310
我叫卡尔德
My name is Kaulder.

93
00:11:49,580 --> 00:11:51,810
请您回到座位上 卡尔德
I need you to get back to your seat, Kaulder.

94
00:11:51,850 --> 00:11:54,520
我很想听听你小时候在塞夫鲁的经历
I'd love to hear about growing up in Sefrou.

95
00:11:56,820 --> 00:11:58,750
你怎么知道的?
How'd you know?

96
00:11:58,790 --> 00:12:00,760
我已经很多年说话没有口音了
Haven't had an accent in years.

97
00:12:00,790 --> 00:12:03,860
我这辈子见过很多的人
I've met a lot of people in my life.

98
00:12:03,890 --> 00:12:06,300
一定会让你大吃一惊的
You'd be amazed what you pick up.

99
00:12:09,730 --> 00:12:12,670
巫师们秘密地生活在人群之中
Witches live among us in secret.

100
00:12:12,700 --> 00:12:15,870
他们的魔力继承自原始种族
Their magic passed down from an ancient race,

101
00:12:15,900 --> 00:12:19,870
已逐渐淡化 遗忘 但是仍然危险而强大
diluted, half-forgotten, but dangerously powerful.

102
00:12:20,910 --> 00:12:24,580
经过几个世纪的冲突 巫师与人类之间达成了休战协议
After centuries of conflict, a truce was forged.

103
00:12:24,610 --> 00:12:26,350
人类允许巫师
Witches would be allowed to live

104
00:12:26,380 --> 00:12:28,120
在世间生存 自治
and govern themselves if they followed

105
00:12:28,150 --> 00:12:34,020
前提是他们严格遵守规定 永远不对人类使用魔法
one strict rule, that magic never be used against humans.

106
00:12:34,060 --> 00:12:36,520
但休战协议是个脆弱的东西
But a truce is a fragile thing.

107
00:12:36,560 --> 00:12:37,590
有些女巫渴望着
There are some who long for

108
00:12:37,630 --> 00:12:40,860
重拾曾经的生活
the return of the old ways,

109
00:12:40,900 --> 00:12:43,600
被黑巫后统治的黑暗时代
the dark days of the Witch Queen.

110
00:12:43,630 --> 00:12:47,000
卡尔德需要解决的就是这些女巫
It is those whom Kaulder deals with.

111
00:12:47,040 --> 00:12:52,010
800年以来 他效命于十字斧教
For 800 years, he has served The Axe and Cross.

112
00:12:52,040 --> 00:12:57,010
与我们共同看守女巫 保护和平
Together we have kept watch and kept the peace.

113
00:13:08,060 --> 00:13:10,020
呃 很抱歉 多兰神父 他在开会
Uh, I'm sorry, Father Dolan. He's in a meeting.

114
00:13:10,060 --> 00:13:11,990
哦
Oh.

115
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:26,010
会议已经结束了
The meeting has concluded.

116
00:13:26,040 --> 00:13:27,510
我以一种截然不同的方式
I serve The Axe and Cross

117
00:13:27,540 --> 00:13:29,040
效命于十字斧教
in a very different manner.

118
00:13:29,080 --> 00:13:33,450
我是第36代多兰 我书写卡尔德的历史
I am the 36th Dolan, and I write Kaulder's history.

119
00:13:33,480 --> 00:13:35,680
我是他的管理者 他的倾听者
I am his handler, his confessor,

120
00:13:35,720 --> 00:13:37,420
我也乐于认为 自己是他的朋友
and, I like to think, his friend.

121
00:13:37,450 --> 00:13:40,190
你完全没有时间观念
You have no sense of time.

122
00:13:40,220 --> 00:13:43,660
我当然有 只不过跟你的不一样
Course I do. It's just different than yours.

123
00:13:43,690 --> 00:13:46,590
我猜你的任务很成功?
I assume your mission was a success?

124
00:13:46,630 --> 00:13:49,530
你平安无事地找到了天气符文?
You recovered the weather runes without incident?

125
00:13:49,570 --> 00:13:51,870
我给你的iPad哪去了?
What happened to the iPad I gave you?

126
00:13:51,900 --> 00:13:53,970
借花献佛了
I re-gifted it.

127
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:55,870
我们不像你那么适应现代科技
We're not all as adaptable as you.

128
00:13:55,900 --> 00:13:57,570
你知道纸张已经过时了吧
You know paper's the past.

129
00:13:57,610 --> 00:14:00,470
它还是非常有用的记录工具
It's also a useful object on which to record it.

130
00:14:02,710 --> 00:14:05,680
你是在回忆路德维希事件吗?
Are you reminiscing about the Ludwig affair?

131
00:14:05,710 --> 00:14:08,420
我现在伤感着呢
I'm in a sentimental mood.

132
00:14:09,890 --> 00:14:11,850
啊
Ah.

133
00:14:11,890 --> 00:14:13,890
因为我的退休?
About my retirement?

134
00:14:13,920 --> 00:14:15,820
所以你回来了
That's why you've come back.

135
00:14:15,860 --> 00:14:17,930
我们一直配合得很好
We have had a good run.

136
00:14:17,960 --> 00:14:20,490
我们解决了许多邪恶的女巫集会
We took out some nasty covens.

137
00:14:20,530 --> 00:14:22,600
你真的准备不干了吗?
You're really ready to call it quits?

138
00:14:22,630 --> 00:14:24,000
区区50年而已
It's only been 50 years.

139
00:14:24,030 --> 00:14:25,800
我好不容易习惯了你
I'm finally getting used to you.

140
00:14:25,830 --> 00:14:27,070
哦 这就是全部原因?
Oh. Is that all it took?

141
00:14:29,870 --> 00:14:31,970
我会想你的 孩子
I'll miss you, kid.

142
00:14:34,580 --> 00:14:36,510
这是支华特曼402钢笔
This is a Waterman 402.

143
00:14:36,550 --> 00:14:37,850
我在上面刻了你的名字缩写
I had your initials engraved on it.

144
00:14:37,880 --> 00:14:39,510
这笔非常稀少
It's very rare.

145
00:14:39,550 --> 00:14:41,150
刻过字后价值恐怕大大缩水了
Probably lowered the value quite a bit.

146
00:14:41,180 --> 00:14:43,120
对我来说可不是
Not to me.

147
00:14:45,990 --> 00:14:49,020
你再好好考虑一下 笔就是你的
You reconsider, you can still keep the pen.

148
00:14:49,060 --> 00:14:51,090
我想你会喜欢我的接班人的
I think you'll like my successor.

149
00:14:51,130 --> 00:14:53,590
我准备用现代点的方法离开你
I'm leaving you in more modern hands.

150
00:14:53,630 --> 00:14:55,560
你曾经说过的誓约呢?
What about the vow you took?

151
00:14:55,600 --> 00:14:59,730
我的誓约是在你身边直至死亡
I vowed to face death at your side.

152
00:14:59,770 --> 00:15:02,570
而不是工作到挂掉
Not to work until I keel over.

153
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:05,140
第35代多兰在你之前来过这里
Thirty-five Dolans have come before you.

154
00:15:06,870 --> 00:15:08,510
这杯敬唯一能让我
Here's to the only one

155
00:15:08,540 --> 00:15:09,840
听取建议的人
whose advice I ever listened to.

156
00:15:09,880 --> 00:15:12,110
虽然你从来不肯照办
Only to ignore it.

157
00:15:13,610 --> 00:15:15,720
但我永远都会听的
But I always listen.

158
00:15:15,750 --> 00:15:17,520
如果你也退休了呢?
What if you were retiring, too?

159
00:15:18,990 --> 00:15:20,790
我是说 如果你的下个任务
I mean, what would you do

160
00:15:20,820 --> 00:15:22,590
就是最后一个任务你会怎么办?
if your next mission was your last?

161
00:15:22,620 --> 00:15:23,690
不可能的
But it won't be.

162
00:15:23,720 --> 00:15:25,030
配合我一下
Humor me.

163
00:15:25,060 --> 00:15:27,730
我一直毫无怨言
I have no complaints.

164
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:29,030
每天我醒来
Every day I wake up,

165
00:15:29,060 --> 00:15:30,670
这个世界都会更轻松地睡去
the world sleeps a little easier.

166
00:15:30,700 --> 00:15:33,030
卡尔德 你经历过
Kaulder, you have tasted more of life

167
00:15:33,070 --> 00:15:35,270
我无法想象的长久人生
than I can ever imagine,

168
00:15:35,300 --> 00:15:39,310
但是你已经很久没有真正的活过了
but it's been a long time since you really lived.

169
00:15:39,340 --> 00:15:41,740
你享受不到我们短暂的生命中
You're missing out on the best part

170
00:15:41,780 --> 00:15:44,180
最美好的那一部分
of our brief stay in this world.

171
00:15:44,210 --> 00:15:47,050
和人分享的那一部分
The part where you share it.

172
00:15:47,080 --> 00:15:50,050
找个信任的人吧
Find someone to trust.

173
00:15:51,850 --> 00:15:53,820
我信任你
I trust you.

174
00:15:53,850 --> 00:15:55,860
可能要再找个清秀一点儿的
Perhaps someone a little more comely.

175
00:15:57,090 --> 00:15:59,760
我知道 我并不像你一样
I know, I haven't lived

176
00:15:59,800 --> 00:16:01,560
拥有悠久而丰富的人生
as long and rich a life as you,

177
00:16:01,600 --> 00:16:03,230
但我同样清楚 人生的意义远不止
but I do know that there is more to it

178
00:16:03,270 --> 00:16:05,570
欣赏一群空姐
than a parade of stewardesses

179
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:09,200
和着月光鸣奏曲进行游行
marching to the dulcet tones of Moonlight Sonata.

180
00:16:10,970 --> 00:16:12,640
你到底是怎么知道
Now what in the world do you know

181
00:16:12,670 --> 00:16:14,980
空姐的事儿的?
about stewardesses anyway?

182
00:16:15,010 --> 00:16:16,640
我又不是生来就是神父
I wasn't born a priest.

183
00:16:18,650 --> 00:16:21,280
我们来干点活吧
Let's do some work.

184
00:16:21,320 --> 00:16:22,820
我知道你觉得这很无聊
I know you think it's dull,

185
00:16:22,850 --> 00:16:25,650
不过我们还是得从头开始
but let's start at the beginning.

186
00:16:48,010 --> 00:16:50,240
虽然是不言而喻的事
It goes without saying,

187
00:16:50,280 --> 00:16:53,010
但您效力的方式真是与众不同
but you've served with great distinction.

188
00:16:53,050 --> 00:16:55,280
冒昧一问 我明天见卡尔德的时候
If I may, when I meet Kaulder tomorrow,

189
00:16:55,320 --> 00:16:57,190
需要冷静一点 是吗?
I should play it cool, right?

190
00:16:57,220 --> 00:16:59,320
仪式完毕再去喝咖啡之类的
No coffee until after the ritual.

191
00:16:59,350 --> 00:17:01,090
别担心什么风度了
Don't worry about your style.

192
00:17:01,120 --> 00:17:02,990
反正无论如何他都会嘲讽你的
He'll take the piss out of you anyway.

193
00:17:03,030 --> 00:17:04,960
但你会没事的
But you'll be fine.

194
00:17:06,030 --> 00:17:10,860
只是 呃 我担心的是卡尔德
It's, uh, Kaulder that I worry about.

195
00:17:10,900 --> 00:17:12,700
你担心卡尔德?
You worry about Kaulder?

196
00:17:12,730 --> 00:17:14,170
你知道十字斧教的前辈们
Do you know how the elders

197
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:16,270
是如何看待他的吗?
of The Axe and Cross refer to him?

198
00:17:16,300 --> 00:17:17,640
他们称他为 "秘密武器"
They call him "The Weapon."

199
00:17:17,670 --> 00:17:18,870
当我提交报告时
When I put in my reports,

200
00:17:18,910 --> 00:17:20,340
他们所关心的只有数字
all they want to know is numbers.

201
00:17:20,380 --> 00:17:22,780
我移交了多少女巫
How many witches I've turned over for detention.

202
00:17:22,810 --> 00:17:24,850
又有多少女巫因为违反法律被处死
How many slain for breaking the law.

203
00:17:24,880 --> 00:17:27,720
这能怪他们吗? 他所做的事情是如此的重要
Can you blame them? What he does is so important.

204
00:17:27,750 --> 00:17:32,090
是的 的确很重要 但他不仅仅是个武器
Yes, that's true, but he isn't just a weapon.

205
00:17:32,120 --> 00:17:34,760
而我们这些知道真相的人
And those of us who know the truth,

206
00:17:34,790 --> 00:17:37,060
必将肩负重任
we bear responsibility.

207
00:17:38,160 --> 00:17:42,900
无论发生什么 发誓你会看好他
Whatever happens, promise me you'll watch out for him.

208
00:17:42,930 --> 00:17:46,300
当然 这是我的工作
Of course. That's my job.

209
00:17:54,710 --> 00:17:56,650
出租车!
Taxi!

210
00:18:38,450 --> 00:18:40,020
你好?
Hello?

211
00:18:40,050 --> 00:18:41,820
卡尔德先生吗?
Kaulder?

212
00:18:41,860 --> 00:18:44,890
第36代多兰昨晚走的很安详
Dolan the 36th passed away peacefully last night.

213
00:18:44,930 --> 00:18:46,960
仪式将在明天举行
The ceremony will be tomorrow.

214
00:18:48,530 --> 00:18:50,960
对此我感到很遗憾
I'm sorry for your loss.

215
00:18:53,400 --> 00:18:56,400
在你之前已有三十六任"多兰"了
Thirty-six have taken the name "Dolan" before you.

216
00:18:56,440 --> 00:18:59,340
你是否有资格成为合格的第三十七任?
Are you worthy of becoming the 37th?

217
00:18:59,370 --> 00:19:01,410
我会用行动证明的
I testify that I am.

218
00:19:01,440 --> 00:19:02,980
你会发誓全力
Do you promise to serve

219
00:19:03,010 --> 00:19:05,210
协助卡尔德吗?
our brother Kaulder in all things?

220
00:19:05,250 --> 00:19:10,050
你愿意成为他的知己吗?
To know him only as he knows himself?

221
00:19:10,080 --> 00:19:12,220
我发誓
I promise.

222
00:19:43,290 --> 00:19:45,390
你就是那个新人
So you're the new guy.

223
00:19:46,650 --> 00:19:49,420
其实我们之前见过
We've actually met before.

224
00:19:50,530 --> 00:19:52,990
很早以前
A long time ago.

225
00:19:54,960 --> 00:19:57,260
你瞧见那些基石了吗?
You see that cornerstone?

226
00:19:59,130 --> 00:20:00,530
我看着它们在玉米地上
I watched them lay it in

227
00:20:00,570 --> 00:20:03,970
一点点地砌筑起来
when this was nothing more than a cornfield.

228
00:20:04,010 --> 00:20:06,870
那才叫很早以前
That was a long time ago.

229
00:20:09,110 --> 00:20:13,400
作为第三十七任多兰 我将自己的生命与忠诚交于你
I pledge my life and loyalty to you as the 37th Dolan.

230
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:16,320
我发誓助你完成组织赋予你的使命...
I swear to help you carry out your duty to the Order...

231
00:20:16,350 --> 00:20:18,490
他们建造这座城市时
When they were building this city,

232
00:20:18,520 --> 00:20:20,590
建筑工人在十八米深的地方
construction crews discovered

233
00:20:20,620 --> 00:20:24,930
发现了一座巨大的墓地
a mass gravesite, 60 feet below ground,

234
00:20:24,960 --> 00:20:27,990
那个被遗忘的角落堆满了几千具奴隶尸体
filled with thousands of forgotten slaves.

235
00:20:28,030 --> 00:20:30,260
知道他们怎么处理的吗?
Know what they did?

236
00:20:30,300 --> 00:20:32,030
不知道
No.

237
00:20:33,970 --> 00:20:35,140
日夜赶工 填平墓地
Worked by night, filled the hole,

238
00:20:35,170 --> 00:20:36,900
继续建造
and kept building.

239
00:20:38,210 --> 00:20:40,980
邪恶无所不在
There are shades of evil everywhere.

240
00:20:46,720 --> 00:20:48,580
我为你准备了
So, I'm sorting you out with

241
00:20:48,620 --> 00:20:51,150
新的信用卡 护照 还有身份证
fresh credit cards, new passport, and a new identity.

242
00:20:51,190 --> 00:20:52,350
我已经习惯用旧的了
Just gettin' used to the old one.

243
00:20:52,390 --> 00:20:54,060
但它们都过期了
Well, it's out of date.

244
00:20:54,090 --> 00:20:56,420
如今的电视台 手机和定位系统
There are global databases now, CCTV's,

245
00:20:56,460 --> 00:20:58,990
都使用全球联网数据库了 世界正在改变
smartphones and geotracking. The world is changing.

246
00:20:59,030 --> 00:21:00,990
只是表面上的改变而已
Only on the surface.

247
00:21:01,030 --> 00:21:03,500
这么说也没错 不过还是要低调点
Right. But it's important to keep a low profile.

248
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:08,740
幸亏这辆车不是红色的
I guess we should be thankful it's not red.

249
00:21:08,770 --> 00:21:10,700
我能问问要去哪里吗?
May I ask where we're going?

250
00:21:10,740 --> 00:21:14,340
我虽然见过别人衰老 退休 去世
I've seen people get old, retire, and die.

251
00:21:14,380 --> 00:21:16,680
但是罕有都在同一天的
Rarely on the same day.

252
00:21:21,420 --> 00:21:24,150
他死在桌子前
He was found at his desk.

253
00:21:36,430 --> 00:21:38,470
我们要找什么?
What are we looking for?

254
00:21:38,500 --> 00:21:42,040
如何知道这附近是否使用过魔法?
How do you know when there's magic in the vicinity?

255
00:21:42,070 --> 00:21:44,340
巫师的魔法来自四种元素
A witch's magic comes from four elements,

256
00:21:44,370 --> 00:21:46,070
火 水 土 气
fire, water, earth and air.

257
00:21:46,110 --> 00:21:47,510
只要用恰当的炼金术触发
Applying the correct alchemical triggers

258
00:21:47,540 --> 00:21:49,480
就能让这些元素显现
will reveal its presence.

259
00:22:04,090 --> 00:22:05,390
这里没有魔法
No magic here.

260
00:22:05,430 --> 00:22:07,530
我只想确认一下
Just wanted to be sure.

261
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:16,470
如果窗户始终是关着的话
If the window hasn't been opened,

262
00:22:16,500 --> 00:22:20,140
这些东西是怎么进来的?
how did that get in here?

263
00:22:20,180 --> 00:22:21,810
只有一个 也许没事
One means nothing.

264
00:22:21,840 --> 00:22:24,550
只有两个 那也可能是巧合
Two, a coincidence.

265
00:22:24,580 --> 00:22:28,020
如果有三个 就是大大的麻烦了
Three, trouble.

266
00:22:46,600 --> 00:22:48,540
趴下!
Get down!

267
00:23:00,610 --> 00:23:02,550
怎么回事?
What?

268
00:23:04,650 --> 00:23:06,150
他是被巫师杀害的
He was killed by witches.

269
00:23:06,190 --> 00:23:07,620
十字斧教的历代多兰
Never in the history of The Axe and Cross

270
00:23:07,650 --> 00:23:09,620
没有一任是被谋杀的
has a Dolan ever been murdered.

271
00:23:10,690 --> 00:23:12,330
你想退出了?
You wanna quit?

272
00:23:12,360 --> 00:23:14,460
不想
No.

273
00:23:14,500 --> 00:23:16,860
我要加薪
I want a raise.

274
00:23:16,900 --> 00:23:18,200
这是在宣战
This is a declaration of war.

275
00:23:18,230 --> 00:23:19,700
谁会这么做?
Who could have done this?

276
00:23:19,730 --> 00:23:21,500
他们使用了隐匿咒
A concealment spell was placed

277
00:23:21,540 --> 00:23:23,270
好让一切看起来正常
to make everything look normal.

278
00:23:23,300 --> 00:23:24,640
他们在找一样东西
They were searching for something,

279
00:23:24,670 --> 00:23:26,610
但不想被我们发现
didn't want us to know.

280
00:23:28,610 --> 00:23:31,210
元素魔法是中性的
Elemental magic is neutral.

281
00:23:32,380 --> 00:23:35,780
追根究底 它并没有好坏之分
At its root it's neither good nor evil.

282
00:23:38,390 --> 00:23:40,860
但这个不同
But this is different.

283
00:23:40,890 --> 00:23:43,160
这是黑魔法
This is dark magic.

284
00:23:43,190 --> 00:23:45,390
非常邪恶
Beyond evil.

285
00:23:49,300 --> 00:23:51,630
他们把他绑在椅子上
They tied him to the chair.

286
00:24:02,840 --> 00:24:05,480
"死亡"
"Death."

287
00:24:05,510 --> 00:24:08,150
那是咒语的一部分吗?
Is that part of the spell?

288
00:24:08,180 --> 00:24:11,550
昨晚 在他死之前你也在这里 对吗?
You were here last night before he died, right?

289
00:24:11,590 --> 00:24:13,520
对
Yes.

290
00:24:16,420 --> 00:24:18,830
让我看看你的手
Let me see your hands.

291
00:24:20,460 --> 00:24:22,400
马上
Now.

292
00:24:30,740 --> 00:24:32,840
在我五岁时
I was five years old

293
00:24:32,870 --> 00:24:35,510
巫师放火烧了我的家
when witches set our house on fire.

294
00:24:35,540 --> 00:24:37,210
我父母死了
My parents died.

295
00:24:37,250 --> 00:24:38,280
是你走过火焰
But you walked through the flames,

296
00:24:38,310 --> 00:24:39,610
把我裹在毯子里
wrapped me in a blanket,

297
00:24:39,650 --> 00:24:41,920
跳出了二楼窗户
and jumped out the second story window.

298
00:24:41,950 --> 00:24:43,880
坠落时 你用身体护住了我
Your body broke the fall.

299
00:24:44,950 --> 00:24:47,390
我说了之前我们见过
I told you we'd met before.

300
00:24:49,460 --> 00:24:50,760
如果你忘了 我再告诉你一些细节...
If you don't remember, I can refer you to the entry...

301
00:24:50,790 --> 00:24:54,600
我没忘
No. I remember.

302
00:24:58,000 --> 00:25:00,700
你追捕那些巫师 将他们绳之以法
You hunted down the witches and brought them to justice.

303
00:25:02,670 --> 00:25:06,210
我一直在等待一个帮助你的机会
I've waited my entire life for the opportunity to help you.

304
00:25:09,540 --> 00:25:11,480
这就是你的机会
Well, now's your chance.

305
00:25:13,250 --> 00:25:15,880
帮我找出真凶
You can help me hunt the witches that did this.

306
00:25:19,790 --> 00:25:22,720
我不该带把枪或者铁槌什么的?
Shouldn't I have a gun or an iron mallet or something?

307
00:25:24,290 --> 00:25:26,530
深呼吸 放松点
Take a deep breath. Center yourself.

308
00:25:26,560 --> 00:25:28,400
当然
Right. Of course.

309
00:25:28,430 --> 00:25:30,230
因为头脑清醒才能抵抗魔法
Because resisting enchantment requires a clear mind.

310
00:25:30,270 --> 00:25:32,270
听我说 麦克斯是一个十四级的男巫
Now, Max is a 14th level warlock,

311
00:25:32,300 --> 00:25:34,600
你抵抗不了的 还不如放轻松
there's nothing you can do. May as well relax.

312
00:25:38,910 --> 00:25:40,240
神父 要尝尝样品吗?
Free sample, Father?

313
00:25:40,280 --> 00:25:42,680
谢谢
Oh. Thank you.

314
00:25:42,710 --> 00:25:44,640
如果是我 就不会轻易下嘴
I'd think twice about that.

315
00:25:50,750 --> 00:25:52,490
我没想到能赚一万美金
I don't know that I can do $10,000.

316
00:25:52,520 --> 00:25:53,820
你很清楚这些虫子
You know the level of enchantment

317
00:25:53,850 --> 00:25:55,460
能对他们造成多大的影响
they are getting from that.

318
00:25:55,490 --> 00:25:56,690
生意不错吧?
Business is good, right?

319
00:25:56,720 --> 00:25:58,590
是的
Yeah.

320
00:25:58,630 --> 00:25:59,760
见鬼
Oh, crap.

321
00:25:59,790 --> 00:26:01,800
关门了 麦克斯
Shop's closed, Max.

322
00:26:14,510 --> 00:26:17,040
卡尔德 好久不见了
Kaulder. It has been too long.

323
00:26:17,080 --> 00:26:19,850
贩卖致幻虫也不犯法吧
It is not illegal to sell mind-altering bugs.

324
00:26:19,880 --> 00:26:21,950
如果用在人身上 就算犯法了
When they're used on humans, it is.

325
00:26:21,980 --> 00:26:22,980
他们把虫子掺进了杯形蛋糕里
They're mixing them in the cupcakes.

326
00:26:23,020 --> 00:26:25,050
我看不到
I hadn't noticed.

327
00:26:25,090 --> 00:26:27,020
那这个呢?
Notice this?

328
00:26:29,060 --> 00:26:32,590
格里芬天仙子 极其罕见并且禁止使用
Griffin's Henbane. Very rare and forbidden.

329
00:26:32,630 --> 00:26:35,630
这是在巫术中使用的 黑魔法
This is used in necromancy. Dark magic.

330
00:26:35,660 --> 00:26:38,830
你知道我不卖这种邪恶的东西
You know I do not deal in these kinds of bad things.

331
00:26:38,870 --> 00:26:42,800
麦克斯 你总不至于犯这种蠢吧
Max, you're too smart to go down that road.

332
00:26:42,840 --> 00:26:45,810
我听过的谎言多到令人难以想象
One can only imagine how many times I've been lied to.

333
00:26:45,840 --> 00:26:47,070
比史上任何人听过的都多
More than anyone in history, actually.

334
00:26:47,110 --> 00:26:49,380
拜托 卡尔德
Come on, Kaulder.

335
00:26:49,410 --> 00:26:51,810
你必须明白 任何人只要敢用这种草
You must understand, anyone who would use this herb

336
00:26:51,850 --> 00:26:54,850
就不会怕你 而这一点吓到我了!
is not afraid of you. And that scares me!

337
00:26:54,880 --> 00:26:58,320
你怕这个 却不怕我?
More than I scare you?

338
00:26:58,350 --> 00:27:00,420
麦克斯
Max.

339
00:27:02,690 --> 00:27:05,930
那个来找我的人皮肤上有种气味
The man who came to see me has an odor on his skin.

340
00:27:05,960 --> 00:27:07,990
闻起来像大蒜 却又不是
A whiff of garlic that was not garlic.

341
00:27:08,030 --> 00:27:11,560
砒霜 还有吗?
Arsenic. Anything else?

342
00:27:12,600 --> 00:27:15,070
腐烂的山楂味
And moldering crabapples.

343
00:27:17,100 --> 00:27:18,810
多谢 麦克斯
Thank you, Max.

344
00:27:18,840 --> 00:27:20,040
小心点
Be careful.

345
00:27:20,070 --> 00:27:21,080
没那个习惯
Not in the habit.

346
00:27:21,110 --> 00:27:23,610
不是你 是他
Not you. Him.

347
00:27:26,780 --> 00:27:30,380
所以 你听懂了吗?
So, all that made sense to you?

348
00:27:30,420 --> 00:27:32,390
你不懂吗?
It didn't to you?

349
00:27:32,420 --> 00:27:35,090
不懂
No.

350
00:27:35,120 --> 00:27:38,560
在内战时期 砒霜被用在尸体防腐上
Arsenic was used for embalming back in the Civil War.

351
00:27:38,590 --> 00:27:40,760
谋杀多兰的那个人
Whoever killed Dolan

352
00:27:40,800 --> 00:27:43,830
很可能住在一个曾经是殡仪馆的地方
is likely living in what was once a funeral parlor.

353
00:27:44,930 --> 00:27:47,740
我们只要找周围有山楂树的就行了
We just have to find one with a crabapple tree.

354
00:27:50,400 --> 00:27:52,370
这是干嘛?
What's that for?

355
00:27:52,410 --> 00:27:54,710
自己打车走
A cab.

356
00:27:54,740 --> 00:27:57,110
接下来的事情你应付不了
You're not qualified for what happens next.

357
00:27:57,140 --> 00:27:58,610
哦
Oh.

358
00:27:58,650 --> 00:28:01,750
好的 我会拿小票的
Right. I'll get a receipt.

359
00:28:38,050 --> 00:28:40,720
哇哦
Whoa.

360
00:29:01,140 --> 00:29:05,010
你妈妈没教你不要吃树上的糖果吗?
Didn't your mother ever teach you not to eat candy from trees?

361
00:29:12,690 --> 00:29:14,620
快回家 孩子
Go home, kid.

362
00:30:01,940 --> 00:30:04,810
走开
Go away.

363
00:30:04,840 --> 00:30:06,070
没事的
It's okay.

364
00:30:06,110 --> 00:30:08,040
- 离我远点 - 嘘
- Get away from me. - Shh.

365
00:30:09,840 --> 00:30:11,040
没事的
It's okay.

366
00:30:11,080 --> 00:30:12,880
别再靠近了
Get away from me now.

367
00:30:12,910 --> 00:30:15,180
- 我不会伤害你的 - 走开!
- I'm not gonna hurt you. - Go away!

368
00:30:16,820 --> 00:30:18,750
没事的
It's okay.

369
00:30:29,300 --> 00:30:31,230
该死
Oh, shit.

370
00:30:41,680 --> 00:30:43,780
你为什么要杀多兰?
You killed Dolan. Why?

371
00:30:43,810 --> 00:30:45,810
谁他妈的是多兰? 哈?
Who the bloody hell's Dolan? Huh?

372
00:30:45,850 --> 00:30:47,110
我这辈子都没见过!
I never met the man in my life!

373
00:30:52,950 --> 00:30:55,660
喜欢我的新钢笔吗? 哈?
Do you like my new pen? Huh?

374
00:31:16,210 --> 00:31:17,910
我想象过自己第一次在
When I imagined my first prosecution

375
00:31:17,950 --> 00:31:19,110
委员会前起诉的场景
in front of the Council,

376
00:31:19,150 --> 00:31:20,310
可我从未想过
I never thought it would be

